OL,3,CResidents told to stay indoors after
OL,4,Cfire at Scottish recycling centre
OL,6,FSeveral emergency vehicles remained at
OL,7,Fthe scene by 5.30am on Monday.
OL,9,FThe service said there are no reported
OL,10,Fcasualties, but residents living in
OL,11,Fclose proximity to the fire should be
OL,12,Fmindful of smoke.
OL,14,FArea Commander David Murdoch said the
OL,15,Fservice would "continue to work with
OL,16,Fthe recycling centre and partner
OL,17,Fagencies to minimise the disruption to
OL,18,Fthe local community".
